## Related Projects

- [Obsidian](https://obsidian.md/) - Great for notes, not AI-native
- [Mem.ai](https://mem.ai/) - Similar idea, but cloud-based and closed
- [Notion AI](https://www.notion.so/product/ai) - Cloud, not privacy-first
- [MCP Servers](https://github.com/modelcontextprotocol/servers) - Official MCP examples

## Why "Proof-of-Monk"?

It's a play on Bitcoin's "proof-of-work." Just like miners prove they did work to secure the network, this proves you did the intellectual work by making your thoughts immediately useful. All those tweets, notes, and ideas become your personal knowledge base‚Äîyour proof-of-work for your mind.

Also, it's built by [@BitcoinMonk21](https://twitter.com/BitcoinMonk21), so it fits.

